    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - INSTALL - REAR AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REAR AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lay the output assembly on its side (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007o6">Figure 246</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007o6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007o6" filename="../figg13/G13007o6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 246. Install Synchronizer Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the synchronizer assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007o6">Figure 246</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the rear auxiliary drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007o7">Figure 247</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007o7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007o7" filename="../figg13/G13007o7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 247. Install Rear Auxiliary Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the auxiliary drive gear retainer and 15/16 inch bolt (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007o7">Figure 247</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Eaton sealant #71205 or Loctite 242 to the retainer bolt threads. Tighten the
                auxiliary drive gear retainer bolt to 190 to 210 ft-lbs. (257 to 285 N&#183;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007o7">Figure 247</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
